er":"Wab Kinew"},{"html":"����� Why is\nthe Premier stacking the deck against hard-working Manitobans who have to pay\nrent each and every month? ","index":"00228","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Mr.\nPallister:</b> Each time the member speaks he stacks the deck against the\ntruth, Madam Speaker. ","index":"00229","speaker":"Brian Pallister"},{"html":"I grew up on a half section of land my great-grandparents homesteaded.\nAnd if the member wants to play class warfare games, he can go ahead and do\nthem. But the truth is, Madam Speaker, that we're fighting for the people of\nthis province who are struggling to make ends meet. ","index":"00230","speaker":""},{"html":"����� A rent\nfreeze is what's in our budget, a rent freeze that protects people. This\ngovernment is here to serve especially those who are struggling to make ends\nmeet, especially those who are struggling to move up in life. They don't have\nthe guarantees the NDP takes for granted. ","index":"00231","speaker":""},{"html":"����� We stand up for those who need our support and our\nprotection. This budget demonstrates that very clearly. <i>[interjection]</i> ","index":"00232","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Madam\nSpeaker:</b> Order. ","index":"00233","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>*</b>\n(10:40) ","index":"00234","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>����� </b>Besides\nhimself, Madam Speaker, this begs the question, who else is the member standing\nup for? ","index":"00235","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Madam\nSpeaker:</b> The honourable Leader of the Official Opposition, on a final\nsupplementary.","index":"00236","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Mr.\nKinew:</b> Madam Speaker, proud to come here each and every day and fight for\npeople in my constituency, like those at Evergreen Towers, who had a\n12&nbsp;per&nbsp;cent rate increase this year. ","index":"00237","speaker":"Wab Kinew"},{"html":"����� Happy\nto stand up for seniors like Deborah Kunkel, who had her rent increased by this\ngovernment by 30&nbsp;per&nbsp;cent. We know how they're 